Chelsea boss, Frank Lampard, has confirmed Edouard Mendy and Ben Chilwell are included in the Blues squad to face Tottenham Hotspur in the Carabao Cup fourth round tie on Tuesday night. Lampard stated this on Monday during his pre-match press conference at Cobham. Chelsea to the game after playing a 3-3 draw against West Brom in the Premier League in their last fixture over the weekend. “Mendy and Chilwell are in the squad for tomorrow,” Lampard said as quoted by Chelsea’s official website. “They’re fit and we will see whether they start or not.” The match kick-off time is 7:45 pm.